<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - FANS AND SHUTTERS - TROUBLESHOOTING - Horton
        Engine Fan With Caterpillar C-10 and C-12
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Horton Engine Fan With Caterpillar C-10 and C-12</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Perform the following three tests in sequence.</para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Fan Solenoid and Circuits</title>
            <para>Refer to HORTON ENGINE FAN W/CATERPILLAR C-10 AND C-12 circuit diagrams in CTS-5122W.</para>
            <table id="t0823403" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Fan Solenoid and Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.56in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.64in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.81in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.78in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.93in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.38in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Check 5A fuse F2 for open condition. Fuse OK?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>F2</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove conn. (335) from solenoid pigtail. Turn key on and measure voltage from
                                    (335) circuit 23 to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(335), 23 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 23, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove relay from conn. (538). Use test lead to jumper circuit 23B to ground. Turn
                                    key on and at conn. (335) measure voltage between circuits 23 and 23B. (Removing
                                    relay may cause diag. code to set.)
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>(335), 23 to 23B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 23B between connectors (335) and (538),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove jumper from (538). At fan solenoid pigtail side of conn. (335), connect 12V
                                    test lead to terminal A and connect terminal B to ground. Does solenoid energize?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The fan solenoid and circuits test good. Perform Testing A/C Compressor High
                                    Pressure Sw. and Circuits.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the solenoid.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing A/C Compressor High Pressure Switch and Circuits</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Perform Testing Fan Solenoid and Circuits (above) before this test.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Refer to HORTON ENGINE FAN W/CATERPILLAR C-10 AND C-12 circuit diagrams in CTS-5122W.</para>
            <table id="t0823404" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing A/C Compressor High Pressure Switch and Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.56in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.64in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.81in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.78in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.93in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.38in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect A/C pressure switch at conn. (311). Measure resistance across the two
                                    pressure switch pigtail terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Across A/C press. switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace A/C high pressure switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect conn. (534) from ECM. At conn. (311) measure resistance to ground at
                                    circuits 23C and 23-G.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(311), 23C and 23-G to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit with 100K ohms or less, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Measure resistance of circuits 23C and 23-G between connectors (534) and (311).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>(311) to (534).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Repair open or poor connection in circuit having 5 or more ohms resistance.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The A/C high pressure switch circuits check good. If you suspect the A/C pressure
                                    switch is not opening properly, install a new switch and test operation of system.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Proceed to Testing Fan Control Relay and Circuits following. Do not reconnect
                                    (534) to ECM yet.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Fan Control Relay and Circuits</title>
            <para>Refer to HORTON ENGINE FAN W/CATERPILLAR C-10 AND C-12 circuit diagrams in CTS-5122W.</para>
            <para>Perform Testing A/C Compressor High Pressure Switch and Circuits (above) before performing this
                test.
            </para>
            <table id="t0823405" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Fan Control Relay and Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.56in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.65in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.81in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.78in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.93in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.38in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove fan solenoid relay from conn. (538). With ECM conn. (534) still removed, at
                                    conn. (538) measure resistance to ground at 23-GA and 23-GB.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(538), 23-GA and 23-GB to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in ground circuit(s) between conn. (538) and
                                    cylinder head ground, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At conn. (538) measure resistance to ground at circuit 23A.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(538), 23A to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit 23A between connectors (538) and (534), then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At conn. (534), use test lead to jumper terminal 28 to ground. At conn. (538)
                                    measure resistance to ground at circuit 23A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>(538), 23A to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 23A between connectors (538) and (534),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With relay removed from conn. (538), measure resistance between relay terminals 30
                                    and 87 (terminals are numbered).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>(538), 30 to 87.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the fan solenoid relay.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With relay removed from conn. (538), use test lead to connect 12V to terminal 86.
                                    Use test lead to ground terminal 85. Measure resistance between terminals 30 and 87.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(538), energized relay pin 30 to 87.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The fan solenoid relay and circuits check good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the fan solenoid relay.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
